<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-75-0617 </DOCNO><TEXT>Dissemination of tumour cells via CSF occurs if there is close proximityof a malignant space-occupying growth to the CSF circulation system.Magnetic resonance tomography is a highly sensitive method that can pointnot only to the pathological process, but also to its localisation andextent, especially if paramagnetic substances are used, to a much moreaccurate degree than had been possible so far with invasive myelographyor computed tomography. (orig./GDG).</TEXT></DOC>